nicholas kristof lecture and q&a events at stanford nicholas kristof lecture and q&a facebook twitter email print add to calendar join two time pulitzer prize winner and new york times columnist nicholas kristof for a lecture and question and answer session on his new book half the sky turning oppression into opportunity for women worldwide humanitarian causes and the role of youth engagement in generating change the lecture is hosted by stanford in government faceaids and speaker's bureau and will feature 45 minutes of lecture followed by 45 minutes of moderated question and answer with the audience the event will be free and open to students stanford faculty and staff and the broader community on a first come first served basis when saturday january 21 2012 7 30 pm approximate duration of 1.5 hour s where cubberly auditorium map audience general public faculty staff students alumni friends tags lecture reading international public service sponsor event is jointly sponsored by stanford in government faceaids and speaker's bureau contact oreid stanford edu admission admission is free and open to all if the event approaches capacity community member admissions will be capped at 100 permalink http events stanford edu events 305 30579 last modified january 18 2012
